column5: PLEASE, I NEED YOUR HELP  !!!!!  Does anyone know how to cancel a bid on E-Bay ?   I put in a bid for a "Mickey Mouse Outfit", and now it seems I am only six minutes away from owning the TORONTO MAPLE LEAFS !
sucks to be you, not even a bad joke.

You could try contacting the vendor (look for ask the seller a question option) to withdraw your bid. If all else fails, you could renege on payment & take a bad report post.  Not a good way to do it but if it's a last resort....  Michael
Have you ever seen how much $$$ the leafs make?  The teacher's pension fund isn't silly enough to sell.
yeah just contact the vendor and they will relist it
You'll get your money back...the product is defective.
ummmmmmm can i get a box seat reasonably priced when the Flames come to town???
Uh-oh. At least I can plead being a newbie fer gettin caught in this one....OOOPS! Michael
Just sitting here waiting for the Canada-Germany game and I thought I would stir the pot

Well.... I could also add that if I was INTO hockey I would have got it.  I'm really not, but once I figured it out, well, it's still a groaner! I heard you gave up your try at standup comedy because there was a bomb threat.....                 Right where you were standing! Michael
It was a REALLY BIG bomb I can't tell a joke to save my own skin!!!!!!!

Actually, I was trying to help someone else solve a bit of a dilemma when your post caught my eye - I really did take it seriously! After thinking it through (meaning I read it again along with the rest of the replies) I got it.  Actually is pretty funny when you take it the right way. You got me good, my hat's off to you!  And Vance, you do have a great sense of humour - you could have slapped me down for my reply but instead you seemed to have enjoyed it!  Cudos to you! Michael
Hehehehehehehe,the Maple Loafs reputation preceeds itself again!!!! LMAO
Now that you mention it Hirk, if a guy who doesn't follow hockey gets that joke (eventually) - it MUST be a heck of a reputation!  Now I feel better??????  Michael
